# Electron IPC surface

- Renderer uses `window.electronAPI` from `src/preload.js` → `ipcMain.handle` / `ipcMain.on` in `src/main.js` and Pattern C services under `src/main/`.
- Renaming or changing a handler: update the owning service (or `src/main.js`), `src/preload.js`, and **every** renderer call site (`app.js`, `history-detail-helpers.js`, etc.).
- Main-process business logic: prefer `src/main-process-helpers.js` / `src/main-process/` (+ `tests/js/main-process-helpers.test.js`) and Pattern C services over growing `src/main.js`.
- AI add-on IPC and catalog resolution stay in main process (`src/ai-addon-state.js`); renderer must not supply trusted model refs for diarization.
